      "appCustomProperties": {
        "state": "engineered",
        "edbb": {
          "role": "exploration",
          "intro": "A long-legged expedition fit built around the size-5 SCO drive and a Guardian booster, then stripped for mass and cooled for close scooping. Initial is a buy-only starter scooper; A-rated is the pre-engineering explorer; Engineered applies the house exploration pattern. The Corsair carries a large ship's worth of expedition kit — its ceiling is jump range, not room.",
          "callout": {
            "label": "Range is the ceiling, not the kit",
            "text": "Ten optionals let the Corsair haul twin AFMUs, an SRV, a repair-limpet controller and a shield without compromise. What caps it is the size-5 FSD dragging a 265 t hull: engineered range lands near ~45 LY — well short of the Asp and Anaconda. Fit it for comfort and self-sufficiency, not for record legs."
          },
          "notes": {
            "Armour": "Lightweight Alloy engineered Lightweight — the lightest bulkhead for maximum jump range; you are not fighting.",
            "TinyHardpoint1": "Heat Sink Launcher for close scooping, neutron supercharging and cooling an emergency high-wake.",
            "TinyHardpoint2": "One Heavy-Duty shield booster stiffens the small shield for planetary landings and glancing contacts.",
            "PowerPlant": "D-rated for low mass, then Low Emissions to run cold near stars; a weaponless explorer needs little output.",
            "MainEngines": "A-rated with Clean Drive Tuning keeps the Imperial speed for planetary work while running cooler than Dirty.",
            "FrameShiftDrive": "The size-5 SCO overcharge drive with Increased Range — the single most important module; the hull's small FSD is what caps the range.",
            "LifeSupport": "D-rate and go Lightweight; long endurance matters more than rating on a peaceful hull.",
            "PowerDistributor": "Undersized and D-rated — no guns to feed, so trade distributor mass for range while keeping boost and SCO draw covered.",
            "Radar": "Lightweight sensors save mass; exploration scanning is unaffected by sensor rating.",
            "FuelTank": "Stock 5C tank; paired with the second tank below it gives long reach between scoop stops.",
            "Slot01_Size6": "6A Fuel Scoop, Shielded — the biggest scoop the hull allows fills the tank fast so you spend less time skimming.",
            "Slot02_Size6": "Guardian FSD Booster — the size-5 unit adds the biggest single jump-range gain available; the Corsair needs every LY.",
            "Slot03_Size6": "A light Bi-Weave shield (sized down, Optimised + Lightweight) for safe planetary landings without a mass penalty.",
            "Slot04_Size5": "Primary AFMU — repairs modules deep in the black; Shielded keeps it alive under module-sniping wear.",
            "Slot05_Size5": "Second AFMU on the opposite priority group so the two can repair each other — standard long-expedition redundancy.",
            "Slot06_Size5": "Second fuel tank extends the between-scoop range for long unbroken legs across sparse regions.",
            "Slot07_Size4": "Planetary Vehicle Hangar (two SRVs) for surface prospecting, geology and Guardian/Thargoid site work.",
            "Slot08_Size3": "Repair Limpet Controller — patches hull that the AFMU cannot, keeping you self-sufficient far from a station.",
            "Slot09_Size2": "Small cargo rack for collected materials, escape-pod recoveries and limpets.",
            "Slot10_Size1": "Detailed Surface Scanner, Expanded — the mapping tool that turns first-discovery bodies into full payouts."
          },
